rompt, then runs the inner test loop. On\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:7:> **See also:** [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:48:The gate is the per-class success criterion for the dynamic-access workflow\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:63:| Output directory | Caller | Absolute staging root for this gate invocation. The caller picks a path namespaced per (library, class) for the dynamic-access caller, or per coordinate for non-class-scoped callers — same convention as [native-metadata-exploration.md §4](native-metadata-exploration.md#4-output). The gate writes JVM-agent metadata to `<output_dir>/agent`, merged trace metadata to `<output_dir>/trace`, and writes durable repository metadata only after the final native-image-utils merge succeeds. |\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:265:| `dynamic_access_iterative` per-class loop ([dynamic-access-workflow.md §6.2 / §6.4](dynamic-access-workflow.md)) | After every class with a coverage gain (Resolved or PartialCommit) | `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/build/natively-collected/<class-key>/` |\nforge/docs/native-test-verification.md:268:The dynamic-access caller invokes the gate per class; the fix-native-run\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:81:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:100:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:119:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:139:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md